  <Investigation>
    <name>Giotto Mission</name>
    <type>Mission</type>
    <start_date>1985-07-02</start_date>
    <stop_date>1992-07-10</stop_date>
    <description>ESA's Giotto mission was the first European deep-space mission flown. As part of the Hally Armada, Giotto was launched in July of 1985, flew by Halley's Comet on 15 March 1986 at a distance of 596 kilometers - returning the first images of a comet nucleus - and then went on to an extended mission to fly by Comet 26P/Grigg-Skjellerup in July 1992.</description>
